race.comment: AQUAHOLIC (4) took a sharp step forward last start at Naracoorte when well supported, only grabbed late to miss by a long neck. That run suggests he's trending the right way and he should look to press forward again despite the wide draw. JUST A BROTHER (5) has been rattling home in his last two, making big inroads from the back. The inside alley gives him the chance to settle closer, though he risks being buried if he's slow away again. HEAD OF THE HERD (1) was a real flashing light at Strathalbyn in a competitive BM58, charging late. Fourth-up now and fitter again, but he's likely to be spotting them a start and will have plenty to do turning for home. WILD WILLY (3) next best.
